<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="locus typicus">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Locus typicus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Surroundings of the Benkovskata Cave, near the village of Cherni Vit, Teteven town district, Stara Planina Mts, Bulgaria, 15-16.11.2013, leg. D. Georgiev, 10 adult, 5 juvenile specimens, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="42.84561">42°50'44.2&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="24.174944">24°10'29.8&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 650 m (Fig. 1).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
